WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.412
NARRATOR:
Previously on Smallville:

00:03.587 --> 00:07.079
ROKK: We've come from the 31st century.
IMRA: We are the Legion.

00:07.257 --> 00:09.088
COMPUTER:
Arrow. Canary. Impulse.

00:09.259 --> 00:12.001
Watchtower is ofﬁcially online.

00:12.596 --> 00:15.929
-Tess Mercer. Acting CEO of LuthorCorp.
-You're my boss?

00:16.433 --> 00:18.389
-We'll be there for each other.
-Forever.

00:18.769 --> 00:20.009
CHLOE:
No!

00:20.187 --> 00:23.429
I have put up with you taking someone
else's side. Clark, then Davis?

00:24.942 --> 00:27.228
DAVIS:
I won't kill Clark if I'm with you.

00:27.403 --> 00:30.110
The darkness.
It doesn't come out when Chloe's around.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.315
She makes me human.

00:31.490 --> 00:32.605
[DAVIS SCREAMS]

00:33.117 --> 00:35.608
CHLOE: Please don't try and ﬁnd us.
-I will save you.

00:38.747 --> 00:41.739
-I took Lex Luthor's life.
-You're responsible for the explosion.

00:42.084 --> 00:43.449
OLIVER:
You've got instincts, Jimmy.

00:43.627 --> 00:46.460
There's an opening on my staff
and you'd be perfect for it.

00:48.716 --> 00:50.877
Say that Clark Kent,
unassuming joumalist--

00:51.051 --> 00:54.794
Steps out into his red and blue?
Creating two completely separate identities?

00:55.973 --> 00:58.680
When I'm ready to tell my secret
you'll be ﬁrst to know.

00:58.851 --> 01:00.136
I'm a phone call away.

01:01.311 --> 01:04.394
l destroyed the Legion ring.
Controlling time is too dangerous.

01:04.565 --> 01:06.055
Be careful in the days ahead.

01:08.902 --> 01:10.312
TESS:
There is a savior among us.

01:10.487 --> 01:13.820
Until you fulﬁll your destiny,
he won't have his challenge to overcome.

01:15.743 --> 01:19.281
-l'm not some problem to be solved.
-I get it. It's too early.

01:23.834 --> 01:25.995
Why are you determined
to see Davis Bloome die?

01:26.170 --> 01:29.333
TESS: The entire civilization's survival
depends on it.

01:29.506 --> 01:30.962
NARRATOR:
And now, the season ﬁnale...

01:31.216 --> 01:32.797
...of Smallville.

01:52.404 --> 01:53.439
Thanks for meeting me.

01:53.614 --> 01:56.356
I'm not the one who had to travel
a thousand years.

01:56.533 --> 01:58.615
Yeah, well, I just hope
that I'm not too late.

01:58.786 --> 02:01.493
-For what?
-The future.

02:04.416 --> 02:08.876
Now I know that any time we travel back
we take the chance of disrupting fate.

02:09.963 --> 02:11.294
To be honest with you, Kal...

02:11.465 --> 02:13.706
...coming back and trying
to change the future...

02:13.884 --> 02:16.000
...I might not have one to go back to.

02:16.595 --> 02:20.383
I don't understand. You said the future
would be safe if we got rid of Brainiac.

02:20.557 --> 02:22.058
Yes.

02:22.684 --> 02:24.675
Everything is safe.

02:24.853 --> 02:26.844
Brainiac is gone.

02:30.067 --> 02:31.648
But so are you.

02:34.071 --> 02:38.235
When you saved Chloe's life,
you saved her connection to Doomsday.

02:38.742 --> 02:41.199
She stopped you from sending him
to the Phantom Zone.

02:41.370 --> 02:45.238
She made him invulnerable
by trying to kill him with kryptonite.

02:45.415 --> 02:49.875
And now because of Chloe,
you cannot defeat him.

02:51.421 --> 02:54.254
I'd never take back my choice
to save her.

03:03.767 --> 03:06.053
I believe yours got a little scorched.

03:12.568 --> 03:15.435
Use the ring.
Send Doomsday to the future.

03:15.612 --> 03:18.604
The Legion's there
and we are ready to ﬁght him.

03:20.075 --> 03:23.192
-The Legion didn't unleash Doomsday. I did.
-Kal-El.

03:23.370 --> 03:24.735
You need to understand...

03:24.913 --> 03:29.577
...that there is nothing on this Earth
that will stop him from killing you.

03:30.627 --> 03:34.370
My father always told me
l was sent here to save mankind.

03:38.468 --> 03:40.925
Maybe this is my true destiny.

03:45.142 --> 03:47.224
How much time do I have?

03:49.187 --> 03:51.439
Tomorrow is the day you die.

04:48.538 --> 04:50.745
CHLOE:
Maybe it's sleep deprivation...

04:50.916 --> 04:55.330
...but I can't exactly see a toga-clad woman
in those stars up there.

04:56.672 --> 04:57.878
It's Demeter.

04:58.048 --> 05:01.381
And her daughter, Persephone...

05:01.551 --> 05:05.510
...was taken by Hades to the underworld.

05:05.973 --> 05:10.888
And Demeter, she enlisted the gods' help
to ﬁnd her daughter...

05:11.061 --> 05:16.306
...but when Hades offered Persephone
her chance at freedom...

05:16.566 --> 05:18.227
...to everyone's surprise...

05:18.402 --> 05:24.113
...Persephone chose to live underground
with the dark prince.

05:28.578 --> 05:29.704
[DAVIS CHUCKLES]

05:30.539 --> 05:33.406
We're actually gonna pull this off,
aren't we?

05:33.583 --> 05:38.703
Find some place to slow down
and build a life together.

05:39.506 --> 05:42.873
As long as we can keep the gods
from hunting us.

05:53.937 --> 05:55.928
Tell me you have a lock on their location.

05:56.106 --> 05:58.939
We traced the radiation on Bloome
after he attacked Neutron...

05:59.109 --> 06:01.145
...but we've got another problem.

06:04.364 --> 06:06.070
What the hell?

06:10.203 --> 06:11.704
Oh, my God.

06:11.872 --> 06:15.410
GUARD: We heard an explosion and then
security cameras and power pulsed.

06:16.793 --> 06:19.045
We thought a transformer
had blown outside.

06:19.212 --> 06:21.874
The orb. Someone stole the orb.

06:22.049 --> 06:25.291
-No one could've broken in without--
-You said the system went down.

06:25.469 --> 06:26.959
Only for a few seconds.

06:30.766 --> 06:32.131
Ms. Mercer, you should know...

06:32.309 --> 06:36.222
...that our security believes
the door was blown off from the inside.

06:37.689 --> 06:41.807
You have no idea
how many lives are at stake.

06:42.152 --> 06:43.642
Find that orb.

07:18.105 --> 07:21.768
Chloe's missing with some beastie-boy
and you're doing what, exactly?

07:25.779 --> 07:28.316
No one wants to ﬁnd Chloe
more than I do.

07:28.490 --> 07:30.776
Except maybe me.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.282
I haven't slept in days...

07:32.452 --> 07:34.659
...and I am dangerously close
to a caffeine OD.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.366
I hadn't noticed.

07:37.541 --> 07:38.530
[SIGHS]

07:44.881 --> 07:46.382
Okay.

07:47.843 --> 07:51.506
Do you wanna at least tell me about
this little novella you're working on...

07:51.680 --> 07:53.170
...that's so important?

07:53.598 --> 07:55.179
No.

07:57.185 --> 07:58.561
Great.

07:58.728 --> 08:01.390
Another ricochet
off the impenetrable force ﬁeld.

08:05.193 --> 08:06.694
Forget it.

08:11.032 --> 08:12.363
[COFFEE POURING]

08:14.494 --> 08:16.109
[PHONE RINGING]

08:25.547 --> 08:27.208
-Hello?
CLARK [IN DISTORTED VOICE]: Miss Lane.

08:31.928 --> 08:33.509
It's you.

08:34.472 --> 08:37.088
I've been searching
for your cousin Chloe.

08:39.227 --> 08:41.263
I am gonna ﬁnd her.

08:42.898 --> 08:45.105
LOIS: How did you even know
she was missing?

08:46.610 --> 08:49.067
I've been keeping an eye on you.

08:50.614 --> 08:51.729
Wow.

08:51.907 --> 08:55.616
To be honest, I was...

08:56.453 --> 08:58.694
...kind of hoping for that.

08:58.872 --> 09:02.114
But I didn't know how to call you,
and all of a sudden here you are...

09:02.292 --> 09:05.659
...out of nowhere to save the day,
and I just--

09:09.216 --> 09:10.251
I'm rambling again.

09:11.468 --> 09:13.800
You just make me so, uh....

09:13.970 --> 09:15.380
[LOIS SIGHS]

09:18.016 --> 09:21.383
I don't know how
I'll ever be able to repay you for this.

09:24.314 --> 09:26.396
You can do me a favor.

09:28.652 --> 09:32.645
-I need you to publish a letter for me.
-What letter?

09:47.337 --> 09:48.452
You're here, aren't you.

09:51.383 --> 09:53.874
CLARK:
You're not supposed to open it yet.

09:55.971 --> 09:59.839
Can I count on you to publish that letter
if anything happens to me?

10:00.850 --> 10:02.681
"Goodbye"?

10:03.520 --> 10:05.852
What do you mean, "goodbye"?

10:09.567 --> 10:12.855
Sometimes we can't outrun our destiny.

10:14.698 --> 10:16.529
But I thought you were invincible.

10:19.077 --> 10:20.533
So did I.

10:25.041 --> 10:26.906
I wanna meet you.

10:31.464 --> 10:34.046
I have to see your face.

10:34.592 --> 10:36.844
I have to see you.

10:37.971 --> 10:40.633
I want you to show me
what you can't show anyone else.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.968
You can trust me. Please.

10:43.560 --> 10:46.302
I'm sorry. That's not a good idea.

10:46.479 --> 10:49.721
Look, you can come through this.
You have to.

10:49.899 --> 10:51.855
And when you do....

10:53.862 --> 10:55.727
How do you feel about phone booths?

10:59.200 --> 11:00.906
They're ﬁne.

11:01.202 --> 11:04.990
Um, there's one on Fourth and Main.

11:05.165 --> 11:07.030
Let's say midnight?

11:08.376 --> 11:10.082
I'll be there.

11:11.046 --> 11:13.162
[hope you'll be there too.

11:14.591 --> 11:16.377
And thank you.

11:18.470 --> 11:20.927
If anyone can save Chloe...

11:22.766 --> 11:24.631
...I know it's you.

11:46.122 --> 11:48.864
DINAH:
Clark. What's the 911?

11:49.542 --> 11:50.918
Thanks for meeting me.

11:51.961 --> 11:54.247
I thought Bart was supposed to be--

11:54.964 --> 11:56.465
Present and accounted for.

11:56.966 --> 11:59.582
-Were you able to get the schematics?
-What do you think?

12:05.683 --> 12:09.801
Geothermal facility,
care of Queen Industries and LuthorCorp.

12:13.566 --> 12:15.477
All right, what's with the black hole?

12:15.652 --> 12:17.938
Rokk said nothing on Earth
can destroy the beast.

12:19.864 --> 12:21.320
So let's put him under it.

12:24.202 --> 12:25.487
The geothermal facility...

12:26.830 --> 12:29.492
...created one mile of tunnels
beneath the Earth's crust.

12:29.666 --> 12:32.157
So it's the ﬁnal resting place
for the bony space invader.

12:32.877 --> 12:36.415
If I can get him down there.
Can you access the detonators in the shaft?

12:36.589 --> 12:40.002
I can override it.
Are we really gonna bury him alive?

12:40.677 --> 12:44.545
Not all of him.
There's still a side of Davis worth saving.

12:50.562 --> 12:52.473
Bart, this is for you.

12:55.859 --> 12:58.020
-What's with the pet rock?
-Careful with that.

12:59.529 --> 13:01.019
It's a very special meteor rock.

13:01.197 --> 13:04.064
It can split the Kryptonian
from the human side of Davis.

13:04.242 --> 13:06.528
OLIVER:
And what if that doesn't work?

13:08.705 --> 13:11.367
What if you end up unleashing a monster
that's unstoppable?

13:11.541 --> 13:13.202
That doesn't have a conscience?

13:13.376 --> 13:15.617
This is the only option.

13:15.795 --> 13:20.164
What about getting rid of the serial killer
before he has a chance to beast out?

13:21.009 --> 13:23.091
You've never wanted to admit it...

13:24.053 --> 13:26.044
...but there is a darker side to humanity.

13:30.018 --> 13:31.724
I know there is.

13:32.187 --> 13:34.894
-l'm looking at it right now.
-Not everyone's worth saving.

13:37.066 --> 13:40.433
-We need to take care of Davis Bloome.
-By "take care of" you mean murder?

13:40.612 --> 13:45.606
Okay, dudes, you guys have got, like,
some serious tension going on here.

13:45.783 --> 13:47.068
What's he talking about?

13:53.333 --> 13:56.496
Oliver crossed the line.
He killed Lex Luthor.

13:58.546 --> 14:00.082
You're making a big mistake.

14:01.591 --> 14:03.547
You're not one of us anymore.

14:05.428 --> 14:07.259
Is that right?

14:35.750 --> 14:37.160
JIMMY:
I'm in.

14:37.585 --> 14:39.621
OLIVER [OVER TRANSMITTER]:
Do you have the decryption key?

14:39.796 --> 14:42.253
-Yeah.
-I hope you have better luck than I did.

14:42.423 --> 14:44.709
Call me when you have Chloe's location.

14:44.884 --> 14:46.215
[TRANSMITTER BEEPS]

14:52.809 --> 14:53.924
LOIS: Ow!
-Aah!

14:55.728 --> 14:58.720
Jimmy, you stepped on my hand.

14:58.898 --> 15:02.231
Next time, don't leave your hand
on the ﬂoor under a desk in an ofﬁce.

15:02.402 --> 15:05.986
I'm sorry, did I just get a lecture
from Jimmy Olsen?

15:06.155 --> 15:08.817
-Who were you talking to?
-No one.

15:12.537 --> 15:15.995
The head of Tess' security has been
staked out at the Talon apartment.

15:16.165 --> 15:18.292
Creepy, but telling.

15:18.459 --> 15:21.792
The only problem is,
her eight-gig mini-brain is encrypted.

15:22.171 --> 15:23.786
Not anymore.

15:25.425 --> 15:26.631
[BEEPS]

15:31.514 --> 15:34.176
Tess is deﬁnitely tracking
Chloe and Davis.

15:34.350 --> 15:38.093
Most of this is from a couple days ago,
but if I can just get in there....

15:42.025 --> 15:43.435
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

15:44.152 --> 15:45.608
Bingo.

15:46.112 --> 15:48.899
Looks like Chloe and Davis
are on the outskirts of Edge City.

15:49.073 --> 15:51.906
Don't take your eyes off them.
Let me know if they move.

16:00.835 --> 16:02.075
[GRUNTS]

16:03.421 --> 16:04.877
GUARD:
Tess.

16:05.048 --> 16:10.088
Lex already tried to break down
the technology of that orb.

16:10.511 --> 16:12.467
TESS: Lex knew that orb
wasn't from this Earth.

16:13.806 --> 16:15.671
lt called to me.

16:16.392 --> 16:20.852
There's life inside it that can't be released
until the Traveler kills the beast.

16:24.567 --> 16:26.558
What you're unleashing....

16:29.697 --> 16:31.483
It could be the end of the world.

16:42.585 --> 16:44.746
DINAH: Clark. We found them.
Uploading their location.

16:51.094 --> 16:53.335
CHLOE:
Please, no! Don't!

16:53.513 --> 16:56.596
-Stop, please! Davis!
DAVIS: Chloe, look out!

17:07.443 --> 17:09.775
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

17:22.291 --> 17:23.542
Dinah? Bart?

17:26.504 --> 17:27.539
What's going on?

17:28.297 --> 17:30.754
Sorry, Clark, we couldn't risk losing you.

17:37.140 --> 17:39.381
[GRUNTING]

17:51.028 --> 17:53.735
Don't worry, Clark. It won't kill you.

17:53.906 --> 17:57.319
This is to get your ego out of the way
so we can do what needs to be done.

17:58.369 --> 18:00.200
CLARK:
Don't do this.

18:14.719 --> 18:17.256
I kind of miss the maid costume.

18:18.639 --> 18:21.051
I've stopped cleaning up after you.

18:21.434 --> 18:23.345
You could've fooled me.

18:24.187 --> 18:27.224
I expect from my reporters
a little better reconnaissance...

18:27.398 --> 18:30.014
...but the bar's always been lower
for you, hasn't it?

18:30.651 --> 18:34.189
Look, I know family loyalty
means nothing to you...

18:34.363 --> 18:36.274
...but I would do anything to ﬁnd Chloe.

18:36.449 --> 18:40.818
And if that means you need to ﬁre me,
pull the trigger.

18:41.329 --> 18:45.618
I plan to. But this actually
has very little to do with Chloe.

18:46.918 --> 18:47.953
[LOIS SIGHS]

18:48.127 --> 18:50.209
You saw it, didn't you?

18:52.215 --> 18:55.799
Seriously, you have a signiﬁcant deﬁciency
of pronoun modiﬁers going on.

18:58.721 --> 19:01.383
-Lois, where is the orb?
-What orb?

19:01.557 --> 19:03.343
The alien technology from my vault.

19:04.268 --> 19:06.008
Oh, that orb.

19:14.737 --> 19:17.149
I guess asking for severance
is out of the question.

19:17.323 --> 19:18.563
I didn't want this.

19:18.741 --> 19:20.697
No.

19:20.868 --> 19:23.985
You just wanna take over the world
with some alien nation.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.494
I am trying to save the world.

19:26.707 --> 19:28.914
What's wrong with Greenpeace?

19:32.213 --> 19:33.919
[BOTH GRUNTING]

19:56.279 --> 19:57.519
[RING CLATTERS]

20:22.638 --> 20:24.378
Keep close.

20:25.766 --> 20:26.926
What's going on?

20:28.978 --> 20:30.559
Sorry about the tranq, beautiful.

20:31.939 --> 20:34.806
We kind of snuck up on you, super-fast.

20:34.984 --> 20:36.645
Where's Clark?

20:43.034 --> 20:45.400
You found a way to kill him, didn't you?

20:45.578 --> 20:48.035
And Clark wouldn't go along with it.

20:48.706 --> 20:52.324
No. He wanted to play devil's advocate
with the actual devil.

20:52.501 --> 20:54.662
Split the Kryptonian from the human.

20:54.837 --> 20:56.793
Black Kryptonite.

20:58.341 --> 21:01.458
Only one glitch in his plan.
The whole beast part.

21:01.636 --> 21:04.673
Last time we checked,
he couldn't control his thornier alter ego.

21:04.847 --> 21:08.681
But I can. As long as I stay with him,
he doesn't change.

21:09.060 --> 21:11.346
Please don't do this to him.

21:11.812 --> 21:12.847
They have to.

21:16.359 --> 21:18.020
Chloe, it's not working anymore.

21:19.403 --> 21:21.189
Chloe, wait.

21:24.325 --> 21:26.361
DAVIS:
Chloe, you're not working.

21:26.535 --> 21:29.072
Davis, just focus on me, okay?

21:29.246 --> 21:31.658
We'll get through this together
like we always have.

21:31.832 --> 21:33.163
I'm
sorry

21:34.085 --> 21:35.120
It's too late.

21:35.711 --> 21:37.827
[GRUNTING]

21:38.005 --> 21:39.541
We need to go, now.

21:41.300 --> 21:42.460
[DAVIS SCREAMING]

21:51.227 --> 21:52.387
Chloe! No!

22:03.239 --> 22:05.946
[G ROWLING]

22:18.587 --> 22:20.168
Chloe?

22:24.844 --> 22:26.380
[CLARK GROANS]

22:31.392 --> 22:32.677
Clark?

22:37.523 --> 22:39.980
Jimmy. The dart.

22:45.740 --> 22:47.025
[GRUNTS]

22:50.828 --> 22:52.318
Whoa.

22:52.788 --> 22:54.779
Check this out.

23:15.394 --> 23:16.895
Your cut.

23:18.647 --> 23:20.262
It's gone.

23:23.694 --> 23:25.685
-Jimmy—
-No.

23:26.906 --> 23:28.897
No, I'm not buying it.

23:29.617 --> 23:33.201
That whole you're here one second
and then you're not?

23:34.413 --> 23:36.654
You took a bullet
and the next day you were ﬁne.

23:36.832 --> 23:39.619
I mean, it's like you're some kind
of super...

23:42.630 --> 23:44.837
-...guy.
-Jimmy.

23:50.846 --> 23:52.347
I am the red-blue blur.

23:54.141 --> 23:58.180
You were right.
About me and about Davis.

23:59.563 --> 24:02.521
You were the only person
who put it all together.

24:03.526 --> 24:05.187
I'm sorry that I lied to you.

24:09.281 --> 24:10.862
I knew it.

24:13.202 --> 24:14.533
I was so right.

24:17.957 --> 24:19.913
Jimmy, I need your help.

24:20.376 --> 24:22.116
Do you still have that wedding gift?

24:22.294 --> 24:25.286
The one for Chloe
that you said you never gave to her?

24:26.632 --> 24:28.623
I couldn't bring myself to get rid of it.

24:28.801 --> 24:31.213
All right, well,
I need you to give it to her now.

24:32.179 --> 24:36.172
And whatever happens to me,
make sure that Davis and Chloe are safe.

24:37.601 --> 24:39.057
Davis?

24:40.896 --> 24:42.727
Jimmy, do you trust me?

24:45.192 --> 24:47.399
Always, C.K.

24:57.246 --> 25:00.659
That is so cool.

25:09.091 --> 25:11.207
[OLIVER GRUNTING]

25:13.762 --> 25:16.504
Chloe? Hey. Are you okay?

25:18.100 --> 25:19.840
CHLOE:
I think so.

25:20.019 --> 25:23.477
-What happened here?
-Exactly what you wanted, Clark.

25:23.814 --> 25:24.894
I split him.

25:25.858 --> 25:28.395
I split him from the beast.

25:28.569 --> 25:29.604
Where did he go?

25:37.119 --> 25:40.111
[PEOPLE CHATTERING IN DISTANCE]

25:40.289 --> 25:43.281
[PEOPLE SCREAMING IN DISTANCE]

25:52.134 --> 25:53.419
I'll get him back here.

25:53.594 --> 25:55.459
But I need you
to detonate the explosives.

25:56.472 --> 25:59.134
OLIVER: You get him down that tunnel.
We'll take care of the rest.

25:59.308 --> 26:01.799
-Can I trust you?
-Yes.

26:04.939 --> 26:07.146
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

26:10.319 --> 26:11.308
CLARK:
Lois.

26:13.822 --> 26:15.949
[CRASHING]

26:22.414 --> 26:24.666
WOMAN:
That's my daughter! Get off of her.

26:25.459 --> 26:26.995
[SCREAMS]

26:27.836 --> 26:29.622
GIRL:
Mom!

26:35.177 --> 26:37.338
[ROARS]

26:40.349 --> 26:41.384
It's okay.

26:41.558 --> 26:43.173
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

26:44.603 --> 26:46.264
[CLARK GRUNTING]

26:50.359 --> 26:52.020
[SOBBING]

26:55.614 --> 26:57.445
[SNARLS]

26:59.368 --> 27:01.154
[G ROWLING]

27:22.558 --> 27:24.674
[ROARS]

28:03.223 --> 28:05.088
He's gonna be okay.

28:05.392 --> 28:06.427
Thank you.

28:08.437 --> 28:11.019
Clark said you'd bring us
somewhere safe.

28:11.774 --> 28:13.264
What is this place?

28:16.945 --> 28:18.105
It's your wedding present.

28:20.741 --> 28:22.948
Or was. Heh.

28:23.118 --> 28:25.609
I was gonna give it to you
after the reception, but....

28:25.788 --> 28:27.574
My wedding present?

28:29.541 --> 28:32.578
It needs some work, I know...

28:34.213 --> 28:35.623
...but so did we.

28:37.007 --> 28:38.543
I just....

28:40.469 --> 28:42.460
I saw us here, you know?

28:42.971 --> 28:44.836
Starting our life together...

28:45.015 --> 28:48.303
...taking something that the rest
of the world had forgotten about...

28:49.478 --> 28:51.139
...and making it ours.

29:01.156 --> 29:04.398
You can see all of Metropolis from here.

29:05.536 --> 29:08.573
From anywhere in the city,
you can spot this place.

29:09.164 --> 29:12.281
I thought that no matter where you were
you could look up...

29:13.335 --> 29:15.166
...and you could see our home.

29:17.089 --> 29:18.795
Could see me watching over you.

29:23.804 --> 29:26.011
I don't know how you do it.

29:32.563 --> 29:34.895
You always seem to come through.

29:36.608 --> 29:41.227
You're always there doing the right thing,
saying the right words.

29:41.947 --> 29:44.279
Jimmy, there's so much
that I wanna tell you.

29:44.450 --> 29:45.986
I know about Clark.

29:47.202 --> 29:48.578
What?

29:49.663 --> 29:51.995
What exactly do you know?

29:52.749 --> 29:55.411
The "what."

29:56.378 --> 29:58.243
I saw him...

29:58.422 --> 30:01.505
...and I saw what he can do. Who he is.

30:03.510 --> 30:06.217
And now I see all kinds of things.

30:07.639 --> 30:10.426
I see what you have sacriﬁced for him.

30:11.351 --> 30:13.342
For everyone, really.

30:16.857 --> 30:20.725
That's the reason I went with Davis,
to protect Clark. That's the only reason.

30:21.487 --> 30:23.603
It all makes sense now.

30:24.323 --> 30:28.817
But the way I see it, you are as much
of a hero as he's ever been.

30:29.119 --> 30:31.576
What you've gone through.

30:31.747 --> 30:34.830
-What you've risked.
-And what I've lost.

30:35.000 --> 30:37.241
I've lost so much.

30:38.212 --> 30:41.124
The only thing I really miss is you.

30:42.257 --> 30:44.418
Well, now you've found me again.

30:55.812 --> 30:59.600
I'm so sorry I left, Jimmy,
but I promise I never left you.

31:05.822 --> 31:06.982
[FLESH TEARS]

31:08.492 --> 31:10.323
[BLOOD DRIPPING]

31:13.288 --> 31:14.619
[GASPING]

31:20.671 --> 31:21.706
Jimmy.

31:27.135 --> 31:28.591
[CHLOE GASPS]

31:30.973 --> 31:32.713
So...

31:33.308 --> 31:37.802
...this whole time
that you were with me...

31:37.980 --> 31:39.470
...it was for Clark?

31:42.234 --> 31:43.815
Davis, just put that down.

31:43.986 --> 31:47.729
How could you do this? I loved you.

31:49.491 --> 31:54.531
You're the only one who ever loved me.

31:55.497 --> 31:57.033
Why?

31:57.874 --> 31:59.705
Why?!

32:00.669 --> 32:02.500
I thought I did.

32:03.213 --> 32:04.828
Okay?

32:05.007 --> 32:08.465
But, really,
what I wanted to do was save you.

32:09.011 --> 32:10.876
Save me?

32:12.639 --> 32:17.599
There is nothing left to save!

32:17.769 --> 32:18.849
Aah!

32:20.355 --> 32:21.390
[PIPE CLATTERS]

32:39.207 --> 32:40.617
[GRUNTS]

32:42.210 --> 32:43.370
Jimmy?

32:44.046 --> 32:47.038
It's okay. You're gonna be okay.

32:49.134 --> 32:50.965
I'm
sorry

32:56.391 --> 32:58.382
I love you.

33:42.270 --> 33:43.976
PASTOR:
He restoreth my soul.

33:44.147 --> 33:48.686
He Ieadeth me in the paths of righteousness
for his name's sake.

33:48.860 --> 33:52.193
Yea, though I walk through
the valley of the shadow of death...

33:52.364 --> 33:56.607
...I will fear no evil for thou art with me.

33:58.120 --> 34:02.409
May Henry James Olsen rest in peace.

34:45.667 --> 34:47.077
Hey.

34:48.462 --> 34:50.327
You must be Jimmy's little brother.

34:56.386 --> 35:00.345
Well, I think that this belongs to you.

35:05.145 --> 35:07.136
He would have wanted you to have it.

35:08.148 --> 35:09.684
Thanks.

35:12.110 --> 35:13.270
Who knows.

35:13.445 --> 35:16.562
Maybe someday
you'll follow in his footsteps.

36:32.148 --> 36:34.013
[FOOTSTEPS]

36:34.192 --> 36:35.807
CHLOE:
Clark.

36:37.070 --> 36:38.856
You're alive.

36:43.368 --> 36:44.608
Hey.

36:50.709 --> 36:53.872
How did you survive
the geothermal explosion?

36:55.964 --> 36:58.580
Just before Dinah pressed the button, I....

37:02.470 --> 37:04.131
I don't know.

37:05.724 --> 37:07.305
I got out...

37:07.809 --> 37:11.051
...before the blast,
but not fast enough to save anyone else.

37:13.106 --> 37:14.141
Chloe...

37:16.359 --> 37:18.475
...l've searched everywhere.

37:22.824 --> 37:24.655
There's no sign of Lois.

37:32.417 --> 37:36.330
I saw someone tacking her photo
on a missing-persons board.

37:37.839 --> 37:41.832
And I keep thinking that maybe—
You know, maybe I haven't....

37:43.803 --> 37:45.634
Lost everyone.

37:56.399 --> 37:58.515
You were there today, Clark.

37:58.693 --> 38:00.194
Weren't you?

38:01.404 --> 38:03.520
I really needed you.

38:04.908 --> 38:06.944
Why didn't you come to me?

38:10.538 --> 38:12.790
I'm the reason Jimmy's dead.

38:14.876 --> 38:16.707
Oliver was right.

38:18.880 --> 38:21.292
I put humanity on a pedestal.

38:27.597 --> 38:30.555
It wasn't a Kryptonian beast
that killed Jimmy.

38:30.725 --> 38:32.556
It was a human.

38:36.356 --> 38:38.893
I was standing right here, Clark.

38:42.904 --> 38:45.316
I know full well who killed Jimmy.

38:50.078 --> 38:52.114
This place, Chloe.

38:54.416 --> 38:56.372
Just get rid of it.

38:57.085 --> 38:59.918
Just walk away and don't look back.

39:00.088 --> 39:01.544
You don't get it.

39:01.715 --> 39:04.081
Clark, Jimmy is here.

39:04.926 --> 39:06.427
He's watching over me.

39:07.012 --> 39:10.379
He knew me so well,
he knew this place would be perfect.

39:12.809 --> 39:15.425
Jimmy wanted to know
no matter where I was in the city...

39:15.603 --> 39:18.015
...I could look up here
and see this beacon.

39:19.983 --> 39:21.769
The watchtower.

39:24.404 --> 39:28.613
Look, Dinah, Oliver and Bart
all disappeared.

39:28.783 --> 39:31.775
Maybe it's up to us
to bring them back home.

39:32.287 --> 39:33.777
Home?

39:35.749 --> 39:37.285
I don't have a home.

39:38.418 --> 39:40.625
I don't like the way that sounds.

39:44.049 --> 39:46.756
I've always tried to forget
I was an alien...

39:51.306 --> 39:53.137
...or a creature.

39:54.267 --> 39:56.849
I've always tried to pretend I was human.

39:57.979 --> 40:01.437
I was raised to believe it was
my Kryptonian part that was dangerous.

40:01.608 --> 40:03.314
But I was wrong.

40:06.154 --> 40:08.145
It's my human side.

40:10.867 --> 40:12.607
It's the side that gets attached.

40:13.369 --> 40:16.031
The side that makes decisions
based on emotions.

40:16.206 --> 40:17.946
That's my enemy.

40:21.127 --> 40:22.958
And Davis proved that to me.

40:23.129 --> 40:26.337
So because of some psychopath
you're gonna cut us out of your life?

40:26.508 --> 40:28.169
Clark...

40:29.552 --> 40:33.795
...human emotion is what made you
the hero that you are today.

40:33.973 --> 40:37.136
They're what's stopping me
from being the hero I could be.

40:38.853 --> 40:42.437
-lt's what the world needs now.
-What are you saying?

40:45.318 --> 40:47.354
Clark Kent is dead.

40:52.951 --> 40:54.987
Goodbye, Chloe.

41:16.141 --> 41:18.052
[VOICE GROWLING AND WHISPERING
IN DISTANCE]

41:27.068 --> 41:30.060
[VOICE GROWLING AND WHISPERING
NEARBY]

42:10.445 --> 42:12.436
[VOICE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

42:23.249 --> 42:25.410
MAN:
Zod.

42:58.576 --> 43:00.567
[ENGLISH SDH]
